snippet.textDisplay: Half the singers say kadam, which is so grating on the ears. Thankfully, the learned half say qadam. With a scholar such as Anwar Maqsood as part of the team, it wouldn't have taken a lot to train the illiterates that the word is "qadam", the qaaf sound coming from the back of the throat. Have some regard for the national language of the sohni dharti. Stop butchering it.
snippet.textOriginal: Half the singers say kadam, which is so grating on the ears. Thankfully, the learned half say qadam. With a scholar such as Anwar Maqsood as part of the team, it wouldn't have taken a lot to train the illiterates that the word is "qadam", the qaaf sound coming from the back of the throat. Have some regard for the national language of the sohni dharti. Stop butchering it.
